sec.p:
The sample size was determined by using the following formula.
n=z2pq/d2×(design effect);
Where, n = desired sample size, z = 1.96 (at 95% confidence interval), p = Prevalence of smokeless tobacco = 27.2% [20], q = 1−p, d = precision level, Design effect = 1.5, = (1.96)2 (0.272) (0.728)/ (0.05)2[× design effect], = 304.3 × design effect = 460 (Approximately).
